50|$|Because {{they were}} de facto governments, {{there was a}} legal {{controversy}} {{about the validity of}} <b>decree-laws.</b> In 1945, the Supreme Court of Argentina accepted them only if they were needed to fulfill the aims of the government. When the military government dissolved and civilian rule was reestablished, the <b>decree-laws</b> were no longer valid, unless the Congress ratified them.|$|R
